17 agency, or any other local public body.
18 (2) 'Ransomware activity' means restricting access to a computer system or its data,
19 typically by encrypting such data, with the demand for a ransom payment in exchange
20 for access restoration.
21 (3) 'State agency' means any department, agency, board, commission, institution, or other
22 entity of the executive, legislative, or judicial branches of the state, including public
23 universities, technical colleges, and other institutions under the state's authority.
24 (b) No state agency or local government entity in this state shall submit payment to or
25 otherwise communicate with an individual or organization engaging in ransomware activity
26 against such state agency or local government entity.
27 (c) Any state agency or local government entity experiencing ransomware activity
28 immediately shall consult with the Georgia Technology Authority. The Georgia
29 Technology Authority shall provide guidance and coordinate the response to such
30 ransomware activity. The affected state agency or local government entity shall be
31 required to provide the Georgia Technology Authority with any information required to
32 appropriately address such response."
33 SECTION 2.
34 All laws and parts of laws in conflict with this Act are repealed.
